{
  "id": "019d3e09-99b2-7492-b08d-9f5b77bb5ee3",
  "content": "# Kernel Event Bus -- Decision Record (2026-03-30)\n\n## What\nIntroduced an in-process event bus (tokio::broadcast) to the kernel for subsystem state transitions. Ships with two day-one consumers: JSONL EventLogger and CLI `corvia watch`.\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n1. **Hybrid approach (D1):** Events layer on top of existing direct calls. Direct calls remain primary control flow. Events are informational and not load-bearing.\n2. **Lean variants (D2):** KernelEvent carries UUIDs and string IDs only. No full data structs through broadcast. Keeps clone cost negligible.\n3. **tokio::broadcast (D3):** Multi-consumer, drop-tolerant channel. Capacity 256 default, configurable via event_bus_capacity.\n4. **Publish after success (D4):** Events published only after the direct call returns Ok. Prevents phantom events for failed operations. 5-persona review caught a D4 violation in CommitPipeline's idempotent replay path, fixed by tracking which entries actually transitioned.\n5. **CancellationToken (D5):** Shared shutdown signal for producers and consumers. MergeWorker::run() checks it each iteration.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- EventBus owned by AgentCoordinator, passed as Arc<EventBus> to MergeWorker and CommitPipeline\n- 5 of 7 KernelEvent variants have active producers (MergeCompleted, MergeFailed, EntryCommitted, GcCompleted, SessionClosed). SessionOpened and IngestCompleted are defined but not yet wired.\n- EventLogger uses synchronous file I/O (append_event) inside an async task. Acceptable at current throughput but should use spawn_blocking if event volume grows.\n- CLI `corvia watch` uses file polling (250ms) to tail events.jsonl. SSE endpoint (Option B) deferred to future work.\n\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering\n- Idempotent replay paths must not re-publish events. Track which state transitions actually occurred, not just which entities exist.\n- EventBus::new(0) panics (tokio::broadcast requires capacity >= 1). Guard with .max(1).\n- #[non_exhaustive] wildcard arms in same-crate matches need #[allow(unreachable_patterns)] but should log rather than silently return.\n\n## What Blocked / Surprised\n- Nothing significant. The issue was extremely well-specified from the prior brainstorm + 5-persona review. Implementation was straightforward.",
